{"questionId":"17351","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The probability distribution of a discrete random variable, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span>, is given by the following table, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"N\">\n  <mi>N</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span> are constants.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7b3066298cc18452fb7c5cefa406775eb349969f.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( X \\right) = 10\"> <mrow> <mtext>E</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>X</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>10</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"N\"> <mi>N</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to find&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( X \\right)\"> <mrow> <mtext>E</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>X</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2} + 1 + 2 + \\frac{N}{{10}} = 10\"> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mi>N</mi> <mrow> <mn>10</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mn>10</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow N = 65\"> <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo> <mi>N</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>65</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not allow FT in part (b) if their <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\"> <mi>p</mi> </math></span> is outside the range <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0 < p < 1\"> <mn>0</mn> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mi>p</mi> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mn>1</mn> </math></span>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17351","referenceCode":"19N.1.AHL.TZ0.H_1b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that E ( X ) = 10 , find the value of N .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Properties of discrete and continuous random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}